4. Unit Testing
What is Unit Testing?

Unit Testing verifies individual units of code work correctly.

Benefits
Detect Bugs Early
Improve Code Quality
Easier Maintenance
unittest Framework
Example
import unittest

def add(a, b):
    return a + b

class TestMath(unittest.TestCase):

    def test_add(self):
        self.assertEqual(add(2, 3), 5)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    unittest.main()
